---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const updated = "2026-06-28";
---

<Base title="Terms — BoltMate" pathname="/terms">
  <section class="section legal-section">
    <div class="container legal">
      <p class="eyebrow">TERMS</p>
      <h1>Terms of service</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated {updated}</p>

      <h2>The deal</h2>
      <p>
        BoltMate is a desktop app that you install on your own machines
        and a small backend service that issues your license. By
        signing in and using BoltMate, you agree to these terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Your license</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          The free trial lasts 14 days from the moment we first
          provision it for your account. It's the same software as the
          paid version, just time-limited.
        </li>
        <li>
          The paid license is a one-time payment of US $14.99 (subject
          to the live price displayed at checkout) and is bound to your
          email address. You can install and sign in on any number of
          machines you personally use.
        </li>
        <li>
          You may not resell, sublicense, or transfer your license. You
          may not redistribute the BoltMate binaries on a paid platform
          or pretend you're the publisher.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Refunds</h2>
      <p>
        We refund any purchase within 14 days of the original charge —
        email <a href="mailto:support@boltmate.app">support@boltmate.app</a>
        from the address on the account, no questions asked. After a
        refund, your license is revoked and the app stops gating paid
        functionality.
      </p>

      <h2>Logitech, Bolt, and Logi Options+</h2>
      <p>
        BoltMate is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by
        Logitech Inc. Logitech, Logi, Bolt, Logi Options+, and Flow are
        trademarks of Logitech Inc. BoltMate works with the Logitech
        Bolt receiver via the same publicly-documented HID++ protocol
        that Logi Options+ uses, and is built to coexist with Logi
        Options+ — not replace it.
      </p>

      <h2>What BoltMate is not responsible for</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Any damage to your Logitech hardware that pre-existed or that
          occurs during normal use. BoltMate sends documented HID++
          commands; it does not flash firmware, modify pairings, or
          touch device storage.
        </li>
        <li>
          Data loss caused by another process running on your machine
          (including but not limited to your operating system, antivirus
          software, or other peripheral utilities).
        </li>
        <li>
          Network outages, ISP failures, or LAN misconfiguration that
          prevent cross-machine sync from working.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Warranty disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        BoltMate is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind,
        express or implied, including but not limited to merchantability
        and fitness for a particular purpose. To the maximum extent
        permitted by law, our total liability for any claim arising
        from BoltMate is capped at the amount you paid us in the 12
        months preceding the claim.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may change these terms when the product or its hosting model
        changes. Material changes will be announced in the app or by
        email to your license address. Continued use after notification
        is acceptance of the change.
      </p>

      <h2>Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by the laws of the State of Indiana,
        United States, without regard to its conflict-of-law principles.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Run by Jared Allen. Reach us at
        <a href="mailto:support@boltmate.app">support@boltmate.app</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .legal-section { padding-block: 64px 96px; }
  .legal { max-width: 720px; }
  .legal h1 {
    margin: 12px 0 0;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4.5vw, 44px);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: #161616;
  }
  .legal h2 {
    margin-top: 36px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    font-weight: 660;
    font-size: 20px;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: #161616;
  }
  .legal p, .legal li {
    color: var(--bm-fg-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-size: 15px;
  }
  .legal p { margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .legal a {
    color: var(--bm-green-deep);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .legal ul {
    padding-left: 22px;
    margin: 0 0 18px;
    display: grid;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .legal strong { color: #161616; font-weight: 620; }
  .updated {
    font-family: var(--bm-font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--bm-fg-tertiary);
    margin: 18px 0 28px;
  }
</style>
